  <section class="readme-section" id="smooth-scroll">
      <h3>Smooth scroll</h3>
      <p>To made a scroll inside a page smoothy</p>
      <ul>
        <li><p>Add <%= link_to "scrollReveal.js", "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jefvannot/web-man/master/source/stylesheets/components/_avatar.scss", target: "_blank" %> and <%= link_to "smooth_scroll.js", "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jefvannot/web-man/master/source/stylesheets/components/_avatar.scss", target: "_blank" %> to your javascript folder</p></li>
        <li><p>Add an 'id' to the element you whant to scroll to</p></li>
        <li><p>Add a link to this element: <pre><code>&lt;%= link_to "Elem", "#id" %></code></pre></p></li>
      </ul>
      <div>

      </div>
    </section>

  <section class="readme-section">
    <h3>Highlight.js</h3>
    <h4>Code syntax highlighter</h4>
    <p>Get the <%= link_to "highlight.pack.js", "https://highlightjs.org/download/" %>
      <br>Put it in javascript folder
      <br>Active it in js
      <br>Choose a <%= link_to  "highlight css style", "https://github.com/isagalaev/highlight.js/tree/master/src/styles" %>

      <br>Store it in vendor folder (middleman)
      <br>Reload server</p>
      <p>For middleman, follow every steps of this <%= link_to  "tuto", "http://www.downrightlies.net/posts/2015/05/06/how-to-get-beautiful-code-embeds-in-your-middleman-blog-using-highlight-js.html" %></p>
      <p><%= link_to "Read highlight usage", "https://highlightjs.org/usage/" %></p>
      <pre>
        <code>
          &lt;pre>
          &lt;code>
          Write your code here
          &lt;!-- don't forget &lt; => &amp;lt; and &amp; => &amp;apm; -->
          &lt;/code>
          &lt;/pre>
        </code>
      </pre>
    </section>

